14:56.463 --> 14:59.762
That's a negative, Cadet Dean...

14:59.799 --> 15:01.960
who really should
be going now.

15:02.001 --> 15:04.561
Under orders?
That's preposterous!

15:04.604 --> 15:07.164
- You were all over me.
- That was my mission.

15:07.207 --> 15:09.573
I seduce you,
turn you into a butterfly...

15:09.609 --> 15:13.101
and then The Monarch was going to tie you
to this huge bug zapper thing.

15:13.146 --> 15:15.774
But you didn't!
You gave me the antidote. And why?

15:15.815 --> 15:18.978
Because I turned the tables
and made you fall for me.

15:19.018 --> 15:21.885
- You didn't even know it was me!
- Well, I do now.

15:21.921 --> 15:25.857
And I put two and two together,
and that equals forever.

15:25.892 --> 15:30.022
All right. Basics. You understand
that you're my boyfriend's archenemy?

15:30.063 --> 15:31.758
You know how this works, right?

15:31.798 --> 15:34.767
I know what works.
I know that <i>we</i> works.

15:34.801 --> 15:37.861
And I know as sure as sugar
that you planned this whole thing.

15:37.904 --> 15:41.067
Yes. Exactly.
That was my big dream.

15:41.107 --> 15:43.974
I wanted to get The Monarch
and Dr. Venture together...

15:44.010 --> 15:46.638
and then do them both.

15:46.679 --> 15:49.671
I'm not willing to share you.
You have to make a choice.

15:49.716 --> 15:51.946
What's a girl to do?

15:51.985 --> 15:54.510
Will you zip me up?
You kicked my moppets out.

15:54.554 --> 15:56.784
Die! Die!

15:56.823 --> 15:59.257
- I killed Hugo!
- You totally missed!

15:59.292 --> 16:00.850
Oh, my God! So wrong!

16:00.894 --> 16:03.692
Solarian has, like,
20/two billion vision.

16:03.730 --> 16:06.893
Cool beans!
The beard comes off.

16:06.933 --> 16:10.425
Hello-ski! I am, how you say,
Russian Guyovitch!

16:10.470 --> 16:13.962
Hank, you should totally grow
one of those! You look like Green Arrow.

16:14.007 --> 16:16.271
Or, like, the mirror mirror version of Hank!

16:16.309 --> 16:19.335
- Yeah, Evil Hank!
- Yeah, Evil Hank, completely.

16:19.379 --> 16:21.176
Crap, is that the time?

16:21.214 --> 16:24.308
Dude, the guests will be here any minute
and I'm not even dressed!

16:24.350 --> 16:26.978
Hello, Rusty,
it's time to get up!

16:27.020 --> 16:29.250
OK, come on,
we've got work to do.

16:29.289 --> 16:31.883
And then, like,
that wasn't enough...

16:31.925 --> 16:35.656
I ended up with a raging case
of crotch crickets.

16:35.695 --> 16:38.095
And did I get an apology? Hell, no.

16:38.131 --> 16:40.395
I got a, "I'll call you."

16:41.534 --> 16:44.002
Still waiting for that chestnut.

16:44.037 --> 16:46.562
OK, Byron, your turn.
Truth or dare.

16:46.606 --> 16:49.439
You're actually talking to me?
Truth.

16:49.475 --> 16:53.241
Did you really think you could get
a bunch of middle-aged men together...

16:53.279 --> 16:55.679
to chase bad guys around
and take it seriously?

16:55.715 --> 16:57.910
Well, yes, I did,
as a matter of fact.

16:57.951 --> 17:00.943
The Order of the Triad
has potential.

17:00.987 --> 17:03.080
Potential?
When JT was conscious...

17:03.122 --> 17:06.250
he was throwing up
artificial cherry-flavored vomit.

17:06.960 --> 17:09.326
And I'm a little
Busby Berkeley myself.

17:11.297 --> 17:13.424
Just don't touch anything.

17:14.634 --> 17:16.101
What could go wrong?

17:16.135 --> 17:18.865
You know I'm on the PA
and not in your mind, right?

17:18.905 --> 17:21.464
What? Yeah.
I wasn't going to push it.

17:21.507 --> 17:25.409
- Good. Now get to the wedding.
- Okie-dokie.

17:25.444 --> 17:28.881
- Good. You going to the ceremony?
- Yes... sir.

17:28.915 --> 17:30.974
The radar's been lit up
like a Christmas tree.

17:31.017 --> 17:34.714
You got to get these radars to
The Monarch, pronto. Keep it hush, OK?

17:38.758 --> 17:40.316
What is that?

17:47.000 --> 17:50.265
- You seen my brother?
- Nah, he's probably sitting down...

17:50.303 --> 17:52.897
torturing Monstroso
with Snapple Facts.

17:52.939 --> 17:56.636
Nah, I don't think... Holy moly!
That guy is almost a truck!

17:57.677 --> 17:58.939
Truckulese?

17:58.978 --> 18:00.309
- Yeah.
- With a "T."

18:00.346 --> 18:02.439
Here you are... and your guest.

18:02.482 --> 18:06.543
Came stag, friend.
This big ol' rig takes up two seats.

18:06.586 --> 18:09.680
OK, but you only get
one bag of Jordan Almonds.

18:09.722 --> 18:12.919
Bride's side,
fourth row, seats 6-7.

18:12.959 --> 18:15.655
- Where am I sitting?
- You are...

18:15.695 --> 18:18.687
next to... Sergeant Hatred and guest.

18:19.832 --> 18:20.821
No.

18:20.867 --> 18:23.335
Look at that, honey!
Look at that!

18:23.369 --> 18:26.236
Tell me those aren't the monitors
from my old hover tank?

18:26.272 --> 18:28.206
What the hell kind of a deal is this...

18:28.241 --> 18:31.802
what kind of a shabby
operation they running here?

18:33.179 --> 18:35.613
You're not gonna
bad touch me, are you?

18:35.648 --> 18:38.014
Do I know?
Honey, do we know him?

18:38.051 --> 18:40.611
No! Hello-ski! I am...

18:40.653 --> 18:43.121
How you say?
Russian Guyovitch!

18:43.156 --> 18:47.115
Sergeant Hatred, pleased to meet you!
This here's Princess Tiny Feet.

18:47.160 --> 18:49.720
Show him, honey.
Show him the little gentlemen.

18:49.762 --> 18:51.286
So she is.

18:51.331 --> 18:54.528
Look at those
perfect little toes, so plump!

18:54.567 --> 18:58.731
Like little nibblets!
Like little corn nibblets!

18:58.771 --> 19:01.672
- Maize.
- That's right, honey!

19:01.708 --> 19:04.142
Hot damn it!
Those things are beautiful!

19:04.177 --> 19:06.907
Gimmie, gimmie!
Gimmie just a little! Gimmie just...

19:12.518 --> 19:15.453
- No way!
- Is that?

19:15.488 --> 19:17.285
David Bowie.

19:17.323 --> 19:21.054
- Brock Samson, it's been a while.
- Not long enough.

19:21.094 --> 19:25.656
You're lucky I don't kill you right here
after what you pulled in Berlin.

19:25.698 --> 19:27.325
You're welcome to try.

19:28.434 --> 19:32.165
- What the hell are you doing here?
- He's giving me away.

19:32.205 --> 19:36.301
You look fabulous!
Thank you so much for doing this, David.

19:37.110 --> 19:39.340
And one, two...

19:43.449 --> 19:47.317
All right. Left foot on the one
but don't enter until the second verse!

19:47.353 --> 19:48.581
I'll know when to go out.

19:48.621 --> 19:50.816
- She's too good for you.
- Are you still mad at me?

19:50.857 --> 19:53.348
What!? I'm suddenly supposed
to be your best friend?

19:53.393 --> 19:56.157
I can't remember a day of my life
that you didn't f... up.

19:56.195 --> 19:59.323
Calm down. Look at all that history!
We have so much in common.

19:59.365 --> 20:01.765
You don't know the half of it, buddy-boy.

20:01.801 --> 20:04.292
What is that supposed to mean?
There she is!

20:04.337 --> 20:05.804
Hi, pookums!

20:05.838 --> 20:08.807
- I feel so dirty when they start talking cute.
- Get used to it.

20:08.841 --> 20:12.777
I wanna tell her that I love her
but the point is probably moot.

20:12.812 --> 20:14.712
Are you reciting <i>Jessie's Girl?</i>

20:19.819 --> 20:20.808
Sorry!

20:20.853 --> 20:23.048
Dearly beloved...

20:23.089 --> 20:26.456
We just need to take it
more seriously.

20:26.492 --> 20:28.255
The séance
was going great.

20:28.294 --> 20:30.353
Don't you remember
how light as a feather...

20:30.396 --> 20:34.025
...and stiff as a board Jefferson was?
- He's still pretty stiff.

20:34.066 --> 20:38.366
And we were able to materialize
a spirit from the beyond...

20:38.404 --> 20:40.804
or at least from a trading card.

20:40.840 --> 20:42.205
Yeah. Poor guy.

20:43.609 --> 20:46.544
Can we take him in the back
and kill him with a shovel or something?

20:46.579 --> 20:48.979
Why am I bothering?
You don't care about this.

20:49.015 --> 20:52.416
No. I care about
the true spirit of the divine!

20:52.452 --> 20:54.682
I care about
the universal truth...

20:54.720 --> 20:58.781
but being a magic super hero
that keeps chasing the same guy?

20:58.825 --> 21:00.383
It's completely gay!

21:00.426 --> 21:02.758
And that is coming from a guy...

21:02.795 --> 21:05.491
that voluntarily has sex with men!

21:05.531 --> 21:07.556
Well.
So does this mean it's over?

21:07.600 --> 21:09.295
- Are we breaking up?
- I guess so.

21:09.335 --> 21:12.827
Do you want me to pack up
my blackula hunter and leave quietly?

21:12.872 --> 21:16.171
Come on, Byron, don't be
so ding-dong serious all the time!

21:17.944 --> 21:20.538
Your Montel Williams
neck pin is blinking.

21:21.280 --> 21:23.544
There is cosmic peril somewhere.

21:23.583 --> 21:26.609
No, no, answer it!
I guess I'll just wait.

21:27.720 --> 21:30.780
It says that Dr. Venture
and his entire family are in danger.

21:30.823 --> 21:34.224
Then there was something about
hundreds of deaths. Like you care.

21:34.260 --> 21:36.751
No! You old bag of sad!

21:36.796 --> 21:38.525
<i>That</i> I care about!

21:38.564 --> 21:42.364
That's the kind of cosmic ju-ju
<i>I am</i> interested in!

21:42.401 --> 21:45.893
For I am, the Alchemist,
seeker of truth!

21:45.938 --> 21:50.136
And I am Dr. Orpheus,
master necromancer!

21:52.612 --> 21:56.776
And he is...
Jefferson Twilight, blackula hunter!

21:59.385 --> 22:01.945
Do you, Ms. Dr. The Girlfriend...

22:01.988 --> 22:05.719
take Mr. The Monarch to be
your lawfully wedded husband?

22:05.758 --> 22:07.453
To have and to hold...

22:07.493 --> 22:09.961
in sickness, and in health...

22:09.996 --> 22:11.520
till death do you part?

22:12.398 --> 22:13.558
I...

22:15.601 --> 22:18.468
Monarch, this is the Phantom Limb.

22:19.005 --> 22:22.065
- You are surrounded.
- Dick move!

22:22.108 --> 22:26.044
You have five minutes
to turn over my girlfriend...

22:26.078 --> 22:29.138
or I will destroy
your ridiculous cocoon...

22:29.181 --> 22:32.241
and all inside.

22:35.488 --> 22:38.423
<i>Ça, c'est de la bonne soupe!</i>

